The paper focuses on a system that helps designers rapidly explore alternatives through mixed-initiative interaction with high-level constraints and design feedback. This involves the use of AI and computer vision techniques to generate potential layouts based on high-level design concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves the use of formalized constraints, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and the use of computer vision techniques, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
